sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects the creation of a new service using the "sc.exe" utility.
Detects an executable, which is not an internet browser, making DNS request to legit popular websites, which were seen to be used as dead drop resolvers in previous attacks.
It is extremely abnormal for svchost.exe to spawn without any CLI arguments and is normally observed when a malicious process spawns the process and injects code into the process memory space.

values.CommandLine: "C:\Windows\System32\netsh.exe" advfirewall firewall add rule name="Host-process for services of Windows" dir=in action=allow program="C:\Windows\SysWOW64\svchost.exe" enable=yes>nul

signature_matches.name: link function at runtime on Windows

rule:
  meta:
    name: link function at runtime on Windows
    namespace: linking/runtime-linking
    authors:
      - moritz.raabe@mandiant.com

    scope: function
    att&ck:

signature_matches.name: link many functions at runtime
signature_matches.rule_src:
rule:
  meta:
    name: link many functions at runtime
    namespace: linking/runtime-linking
    authors:
      - moritz.raabe@mandiant.com
      - joakim@intezer.com
    scope: function
    att&ck:
      - Execution::Shared Modules [T1129]
    examples:
      - b7b5e1253710d8927cbe07d52d2d2e10:0x401000
  features:
    - or:
      - and:
        - os: windows
        - match: link function at runtime on Windows
        - or:
          - count(api(kernel32.GetProcAddress)): 5 or more
          - count(api(ntdll.LdrGetProcedureAddress)): 5 or more
      - and:
        - os: linux
        - match: link function at runtime on Linux
        - or:
          - count(api(dlsym)): 5 or more
          - count(api(dlvsym)): 5 or more

signature_matches.name: get geographical location
signature_matches.rule_src:
# generated using capa explorer for IDA Pro
rule:
  meta:
    name: get geographical location
    namespace: collection
    authors:
      - moritz.raabe
      - michael.hunhoff@mandiant.com
    scope: function
    att&ck:
      - Discovery::System Location Discovery [T1614]
    examples:
      - 9879D201DC5ACA863F357184CD1F170E:0x10001A99
  features:
    - or:
      - api: GetLocaleInfo
      - api: GetLocaleInfoEx
      - api: kernel32.GetUserGeoID
      - api: kernel32.GetGeoInfo
      # strings part of requests or parsed from response
      # "geo" and "zip" are too short
      # "region" results in FPs mostly related to memory
      - string: /geolocation/i
      - string: /geo-location/i
      - string: /^city/i
      - string: /region_code/i
      - string: /region_name/i
      - string: /^country/i
      - string: /country_code/i
      - string: /countrycode/i
      - string: /country_name/i
      - string: /continent_code/i
      - string: /continent_name/i
      - string: /^latitude/i
      - string: /^longitude/i

signature_matches.name: check for software breakpoints
signature_matches.rule_src:
rule:
  meta:
    name: check for software breakpoints
    namespace: anti-analysis/anti-debugging/debugger-detection
    authors:
      - michael.hunhoff@mandiant.com
    scope: function
    mbc:
      - Anti-Behavioral Analysis::Debugger Detection::Software Breakpoints [B0001.025]
    references:
      - https://github.com/LordNoteworthy/al-khaser/blob/master/al-khaser/AntiDebug/SoftwareBreakpoints.cpp
      - https://anti-debug.checkpoint.com/techniques/assembly.html
    examples:
      - al-khaser_x86.exe_:0x431020
  features:
    - and:
      - or:
        - instruction:
          - mnemonic: cmp
          - number: 0xCC = INT3
        - and:
          - description: INT3 (long form)
          - instruction:
            - mnemonic: cmp
            - number: 0xCD = INT3 (long form byte 1)
          - instruction:
            - mnemonic: cmp
            - number: 0x03 = INT3 (long form byte 2)
      - match: contain loop
